title: Dishwasher Float Switch
description: Dishwasher Float Switch ★★★★★ ★★★★★ 2 Reviews PartSelect Number PS3492842 Manufacturer Part Number 154773201 Water that fills your dishwasher lifts the float. When it reaches a certain level, the float triggers the float switch to shut off, thereby shutting off the flow of water into the dishwasher.

installationInstructions.author: steve from virginia beach, VA
installationInstructions.title: No water to dish washer
installationInstructions.content: After figuring out the problem wasn't the water inlet switch, I replaced the switch assembly for the water level float. Cut off supply water to dishwasher, removed the 2 screws holding switch assembly, and installed new switch. 15 minutes, very easy job.
